sql:
SELECT agency_name, location
FROM escort_agencies
WHERE verified = 1;

SELECT agency_name, contact_email, location
FROM escort_agencies
WHERE verified = 1 AND num_reviews > (SELECT AVG(num_reviews) FROM escort_agencies);

SELECT agency_name, contact_email, phone_number, location, rating, num_reviews, verified, registration_date
FROM escort_agencies
ORDER BY rating DESC;

external_knowledge:
- In this metaphorical context, "beacon lights" symbolize the agency identifiers and names that help identify each escort agency;
- "Financial waters" represent the monetary transactions or payments;
- "Average earnings" refers to the average payment made to the escorts;
- "Harbor" symbolizes the escort agencies where the escorts, or "professional companions," are registered or work.

sql:
SELECT agency_name, rating, num_reviews 
FROM escort_agencies 
ORDER BY num_reviews DESC;

SELECT agency_id, num_reviews
FROM escort_agencies
ORDER BY num_reviews DESC;

SELECT AVG(rating) 
FROM advertisements 
WHERE agency_id = 4;

SELECT agency_name, rating AS average_rating
FROM escort_agencies
WHERE verified = 1 AND rating >= 4.0;

SELECT escort_name, rate
FROM escort_profiles
ORDER BY rate DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "sailing vessels" metaphorically refers to the users;
- "embarked on their journey" and "latest voyages" refer metaphorically to the users' first and last posts;
- "departure and arrival dates" are the dates when the first and last posts were made;
- "names of the ports" refer to the forum names where the users first and last posted;
- "titles of their first and last voyages" are the titles of the first and last posts made.

sql:
SELECT escort_name
FROM escort_profiles
WHERE rate > (SELECT AVG(rate) FROM escort_profiles);

SELECT agency_name, rating
FROM escort_agencies
ORDER BY rating DESC;

SELECT agency_name, location, num_reviews AS total_reviews
FROM escort_agencies
ORDER BY num_reviews DESC;

external_knowledge:
- 'more expensive escorts' refers to escorts with a rate greater than 200;
- 'visited frequently' implies more than 10 access events;
- 'reputable agencies' indicate agencies that are verified.
